 795:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c **** /**
 796:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * Sends an IP packet on a network interface. This function constructs
 797:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * the IP header and calculates the IP header checksum. If the source
 798:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * IP address is NULL, the IP address of the outgoing network
 799:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * interface is filled in as source address.
 800:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * If the destination IP address is LWIP_IP_HDRINCL, p is assumed to already
 801:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * include an IP header and p->payload points to it instead of the data.
 802:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  *
 803:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @param p the packet to send (p->payload points to the data, e.g. next
 804:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****             protocol header; if dest == LWIP_IP_HDRINCL, p already includes an
 805:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****             IP header and p->payload points to that IP header)
 806:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @param src the source IP address to send from (if src == IP4_ADDR_ANY, the
 807:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  *         IP  address of the netif used to send is used as source address)
ARM GAS  C:\Users\hh\AppData\Local\Temp\ccnwDiiP.s 			page 31


 808:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @param dest the destination IP address to send the packet to
 809:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @param ttl the TTL value to be set in the IP header
 810:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @param tos the TOS value to be set in the IP header
 811:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @param proto the PROTOCOL to be set in the IP header
 812:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @param netif the netif on which to send this packet
 813:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @return ERR_OK if the packet was sent OK
 814:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  *         ERR_BUF if p doesn't have enough space for IP/LINK headers
 815:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  *         returns errors returned by netif->output
 816:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  *
 817:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  * @note ip_id: RFC791 "some host may be able to simply use
 818:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  *  unique identifiers independent of destination"
 819:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c ****  */
 820:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/ipv4/ip4.c **** err_t
